    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The behavior is imho perfect right now. The proposes improvement is to set the cursor when hovering the minimal value (when it is selected) to the default, not the hand. Because the hand is for clickable items and when it is the current value, clicking on it does not do anything therefore it is not clickable. Does that make sense? It's hard to explain. I will provide a PR (simple css fix) it should be easier to get :)",
